The paper focuses on evaluating 3D correspondence grouping algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as shape retrieval, object recognition, and point cloud registration. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with robotics (cs.RO) as it evaluates algorithms for 3D object recognition, which is a crucial task in robotics. The paper also addresses the issue of noise, clutter, and occlusion, which are common in graphics (cs.GR). The evaluation of algorithms is based on quantitative outcomes, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
